    {
      "id": "C5pkbEs2MFCtJ0EbyelKu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -343.38737099256446,
      "y": 5811.008819853505,
      "width": 1168.199462890625,
      "height": 360,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 419066420,
      "version": 218,
      "versionNonce": 980431176,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774276737977,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Django inbuild User has lot of fields like\nfirst_name\nlast_name\nemail\npassword\nusername\ngroup and others\nand function for authentication like is_authenticated & all",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Django inbuild User has lot of fields like\nfirst_name\nlast_name\nemail\npassword\nusername\ngroup and others\nand function for authentication like is_authenticated & all",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "iRtdTcKYRUfLkW27lJTj_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 208.79285650186125,
      "y": 5787.088808705233,
      "width": 19.79998779296875,
      "height": 45,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bII",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 379440012,
      "version": 3,
      "versionNonce": 542590516,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770139037606,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "jmL_8kYGtzCx_x4Tbb7dM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -480.3375782807472,
      "y": 6344.391797835666,
      "width": 2514.5986328125,
      "height": 720,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 683254540,
      "version": 824,
      "versionNonce": 148662072,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774276737977,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "But today's modern app needed phone_number, profile_image, date_of_birth, gender and lot of other fields\nas per app requirement\n\nso to create as per our requirement we need to customize.\n\nTo customise django provide two inbuilt classes, using that we can customise our User model\nAbstractUser\nAbstractBaseUser\n\nWhat are the diff in these two classes ?\n\n\nif we want to use django User default fields like first_name, last_name, email, password, username and apart of this we can add\ndifferenct fields as per our requirement then we can user AbstractUser.\n\nIf we want everything new but we need authentication functionality then we can use  AbstractBaseUser",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "But today's modern app needed phone_number, profile_image, date_of_birth, gender and lot of other fields\nas per app requirement\n\nso to create as per our requirement we need to customize.\n\nTo customise django provide two inbuilt classes, using that we can customise our User model\nAbstractUser\nAbstractBaseUser\n\nWhat are the diff in these two classes ?\n\n\nif we want to use django User default fields like first_name, last_name, email, password, username and apart of this we can add\ndifferenct fields as per our requirement then we can user AbstractUser.\n\nIf we want everything new but we need authentication functionality then we can use  AbstractBaseUser",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "D58Gs2cK4ZIEFfK5bscqh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -462.88962228792536,
      "y": 7336.9206445888685,
      "width": 2158.19873046875,
      "height": 3690,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2045379340,
      "version": 1217,
      "versionNonce": 1324009544,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774276737977,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "By default django uses username & password for login, but we are making one app in which we want to login\nvia email or phone_number or employee_id \n\n\nLets say we want to do login via phone number then phone_number should be unique\nand username = None\n\nand we need to add that field in USERNAME_FIELD\n\nUSERNAME_FIELD = 'phone_number'\nif we want some fields mandatory while User creation then we can add in REQUIRED_FIELD\n\nREQUIRED_FIELD = []\n\nwe need to create our own customUserManager as well due to default manager knows username and password\nwill come during login but we are sending phone_number so we need to write our own CustomUserManager as well.\nand we need to tell our manager that we have added some extra fields please take care of these as well.\n\nafter creating CustomUser model we need to tell django also please use this model for user\n\nin settings.py\n\nAUTH_USER_MODEL = 'accounts.CustomUser'.  # 'app_name.model_name'\n\n\nmodels.py\n\nfrom django.db import models\nfrom django.contrib.auth.models import AbstractUser\nfrom .managers import CustomUserManager\n\nclass CustomUser(AbstractUser):\n    username = None\n    phone_number = models.CharField(max_length=15, unique=True)\n    profile_image = models.ImageField(upload_to='profile_images/', null=True, blank=True)\n    is_verified = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n\n    USERNAME_FIELD = 'phone_number'\n\n    objects = CustomUserManager()\n\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return self.phone_number\n\n\n\nmanagers.py\n\nfrom django.contrib.auth.models import BaseUserManager\n\nclass CustomUserManager(BaseUserManager):\n    def create_user(self, phone_number, password=None, **extra_fields):\n        if not phone_number:\n            raise ValueError('The Phone Number must be set')\n        user = self.model(phone_number=phone_number, **extra_fields)\n        user.set_password(password)\n        user.save(using=self._db)\n        return user\n\n    def create_superuser(self, phone_number, password=None, **extra_fields):\n        extra_fields.setdefault('is_staff', True)\n        extra_fields.setdefault('is_superuser', True)\n        extra_fields.setdefault('is_active', True)\n\n\n        if extra_fields.get('is_staff') is not True:\n            raise ValueError('Superuser must have is_staff=True.')\n        if extra_fields.get('is_superuser') is not True:\n            raise ValueError('Superuser must have is_superuser=True.')\n\n        if extra_fields.get('is_active') is not True:\n            raise ValueError('Superuser must have is_active=True.')\n\n        return self.create_user(phone_number, password, **extra_fields)\n\n\nsettings.py\n\nAUTH_USER_MODEL = 'accounts.CustomUser'\n\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "By default django uses username & password for login, but we are making one app in which we want to login\nvia email or phone_number or employee_id \n\n\nLets say we want to do login via phone number then phone_number should be unique\nand username = None\n\nand we need to add that field in USERNAME_FIELD\n\nUSERNAME_FIELD = 'phone_number'\nif we want some fields mandatory while User creation then we can add in REQUIRED_FIELD\n\nREQUIRED_FIELD = []\n\nwe need to create our own customUserManager as well due to default manager knows username and password\nwill come during login but we are sending phone_number so we need to write our own CustomUserManager as well.\nand we need to tell our manager that we have added some extra fields please take care of these as well.\n\nafter creating CustomUser model we need to tell django also please use this model for user\n\nin settings.py\n\nAUTH_USER_MODEL = 'accounts.CustomUser'.  # 'app_name.model_name'\n\n\nmodels.py\n\nfrom django.db import models\nfrom django.contrib.auth.models import AbstractUser\nfrom .managers import CustomUserManager\n\nclass CustomUser(AbstractUser):\n    username = None\n    phone_number = models.CharField(max_length=15, unique=True)\n    profile_image = models.ImageField(upload_to='profile_images/', null=True, blank=True)\n    is_verified = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n\n    USERNAME_FIELD = 'phone_number'\n\n    objects = CustomUserManager()\n\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return self.phone_number\n\n\n\nmanagers.py\n\nfrom django.contrib.auth.models import BaseUserManager\n\nclass CustomUserManager(BaseUserManager):\n    def create_user(self, phone_number, password=None, **extra_fields):\n        if not phone_number:\n            raise ValueError('The Phone Number must be set')\n        user = self.model(phone_number=phone_number, **extra_fields)\n        user.set_password(password)\n        user.save(using=self._db)\n        return user\n\n    def create_superuser(self, phone_number, password=None, **extra_fields):\n        extra_fields.setdefault('is_staff', True)\n        extra_fields.setdefault('is_superuser', True)\n        extra_fields.setdefault('is_active', True)\n\n\n        if extra_fields.get('is_staff') is not True:\n            raise ValueError('Superuser must have is_staff=True.')\n        if extra_fields.get('is_superuser') is not True:\n            raise ValueError('Superuser must have is_superuser=True.')\n\n        if extra_fields.get('is_active') is not True:\n            raise ValueError('Superuser must have is_active=True.')\n\n        return self.create_user(phone_number, password, **extra_fields)\n\n\nsettings.py\n\nAUTH_USER_MODEL = 'accounts.CustomUser'\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "bYYLwsmy3nI7-INxFf1JA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1678.6169100407787,
      "y": -2208.138621778424,
      "width": 759,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 931834952,
      "version": 83,
      "versionNonce": 968638792,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774276737589,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Got it—you want to reach a level where **you can write ANY Django ORM\nquery and also explain it confidently (like in interviews or real\nprojects)**.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Got it—you want to reach a level where **you can write ANY Django ORM query and also explain it confidently (like in interviews or real projects)**.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
