      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "from django.utils import timezone\nfrom datetime import timedelta\n\nOrder.objects.filter(\n    created_at__gte=timezone.now() - timedelta(days=7)\n)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "from django.utils import timezone\nfrom datetime import timedelta\n\nOrder.objects.filter(\n    created_at__gte=timezone.now() - timedelta(days=7)\n)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "JCz5OGsJI3kIa-WMDEVVB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -330.79269129077875,
      "y": -6089.544871778424,
      "width": 803,
      "height": 6700,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2134822200,
      "version": 591,
      "versionNonce": 202095928,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774279031151,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n\n---\n\n# 🧩 SETUP (Assume Models)\n\nclass User(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n    age = models.IntegerField()\n\nclass Product(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n    price = models.FloatField()\n\nclass Order(models.Model):\n    user = models.ForeignKey(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    created_at = models.DateTimeField()\n\nclass OrderItem(models.Model):\n    order = models.ForeignKey(Order, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    product = models.ForeignKey(Product, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    quantity = models.IntegerField()\n\n---\n\n# 🟡 LEVEL 1 (Core Understanding)\n\n### 1. Get all users whose age > 25\nUser.objects.filter(age__gt=25)\n\n\n### 2. Get users whose name contains \"amit\"\nUser.objects.filter(name__icontains=\"amit\")\n\n\n### 3. Get latest 5 orders\nOrder.objects.order_by(\"-created_at\")[:5]\n\n### 4. Count total users\nUser.objects.count()\n\n### 5. Get all product names only\nProduct.objects.values_list(\"name\", flat=True)\n\n\n\n# 🟠 LEVEL 2 (JOINS & RELATIONSHIPS)\n\n### 6. Get all orders for user \"Amit\"\nOrder.objects.filter(user__name=\"Amit\")\n\n\n### 7. Get users who have placed at least 1 order\nUser.objects.filter(order__isnull=False).distinct()\n\n\n### 8. Get users with NO orders\nUser.objects.filter(order__isnull=True)\n\n\n### 9. Get all order items where product price > 100\nOrderItem.objects.filter(product__price__gt=100)\n\n\n### 10. Fetch orders with user data optimized\nOrder.objects.select_related(\"user\")\n\n\n🔵 LEVEL 3 (AGGREGATION & GROUP BY)\n\n### 11. Count orders per user\nfrom django.db.models import Count\nUser.objects.annotate(order_count=Count(\"order\"))\n\n\n### 12. Users with more than 3 orders\nUser.objects.annotate(order_count=Count(\"order\"))\\\n            .filter(order_count__gt=3)\n\n\n### 13. Total quantity sold per product\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    total_sold=Count(\"orderitem\")\n)\n\n\n👉 (Better version below 👇)\nfrom django.db.models import Sum\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    total_sold=Sum(\"orderitem__quantity\")\n)\n\n\n### 14. Average product price\nfrom django.db.models import Avg\nProduct.objects.aggregate(avg_price=Avg(\"price\"))\n\n\n### 15. Total revenue per order\nfrom django.db.models import Sum, F\n\nOrder.objects.annotate(\n    total=Sum(F(\"orderitem__quantity\") * F(\"orderitem__product__price\"))\n)\n\n\n🔴 LEVEL 4 (ADVANCED QUERIES 🔥)\n\n### 16. Get latest order per user\n\nfrom django.db.models import OuterRef, Subquery\n\nlatest_order = Order.objects.filter(user=OuterRef(\"pk\"))\\\n                            .order_by(\"-created_at\")\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    latest_order_id=Subquery(latest_order.values(\"id\")[:1])\n)\n\n\n### 17. Users who ordered a specific product\nUser.objects.filter(order__orderitem__product__name=\"Laptop\").distinct()\n\n\n### 18. Orders with total > 1000\nOrder.objects.annotate(\n    total=Sum(F(\"orderitem__quantity\") * F(\"orderitem__product__price\"))\n).filter(total__gt=1000)\n\n\n### 19. Products never ordered\nProduct.objects.filter(orderitem__isnull=True)\n\n\n### 20. Users with at least 1 expensive product (>500)\nUser.objects.filter(\n    order__orderitem__product__price__gt=500\n).distinct()\n\n\n# ⚡ LEVEL 5 (EXPERT 🔥🔥🔥)\n\n### 21. Users whose total spending > 5000\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    total_spent=Sum(\n        F(\"order__orderitem__quantity\") *\n        F(\"order__orderitem__product__price\")\n    )\n).filter(total_spent__gt=5000)\n\n\n### 22. Most sold product\n\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    total_sold=Sum(\"orderitem__quantity\")\n).order_by(\"-total_sold\").first()\n\n\n### 23. Users who placed order in last 7 days\n\nfrom django.utils import timezone\nfrom datetime import timedelta\n\nUser.objects.filter(\n    order__created_at__gte=timezone.now() - timedelta(days=7)\n).distinct()\n\n\n### 24. Orders having more than 3 items\nOrder.objects.annotate(\n    item_count=Count(\"orderitem\")\n).filter(item_count__gt=3)\n\n\n### 25. Products with highest revenue\n\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    revenue=Sum(\n        F(\"orderitem__quantity\") * F(\"price\")\n    )\n).order_by(\"-revenue\")\n\n\n\n### 26. Check if user has orders (efficient)\nfrom django.db.models import Exists, OuterRef\n\norders = Order.objects.filter(user=OuterRef(\"pk\"))\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    has_orders=Exists(orders)\n)\n\n\n### 27. Get first order date per user\nfrom django.db.models import Min\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    first_order=Min(\"order__created_at\")\n)\n\n\n### 28. Users who bought ALL products (hard)\n\n👉 Concept: count match\n\n\nfrom django.db.models import Count\n\ntotal_products = Product.objects.count()\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    product_count=Count(\"order__orderitem__product\", distinct=True)\n).filter(product_count=total_products)\n\n\n### 29. Duplicate users by name\n\nUser.objects.values(\"name\")\\\n    .annotate(count=Count(\"id\"))\\\n    .filter(count__gt=1)\n\n\n### 30. Top 3 users by spending\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    total_spent=Sum(\n        F(\"order__orderitem__quantity\") *\n        F(\"order__orderitem__product__price\")\n    )\n).order_by(\"-total_spent\")[:3]\n\n\n\n# 🧠 HOW TO MASTER (IMPORTANT)\n\nIf you truly want to reach **“I can write anything” level**, follow this:\n\n### 🔁 Practice Loop\n\n1. Convert problem → SQL\n2. SQL → ORM\n3. Optimize query\n\n---\n\n### 🔥 Key Patterns You Must Master\n\n* `filter(user__order__...)` → JOIN chaining\n* `annotate()` → GROUP BY\n* `Subquery + OuterRef` → nested queries\n* `Exists` → performance optimization\n* `F()` → field vs field operations\n\n---\n\n# 🚀 NEXT STEP (Highly Recommended)\n\nIf you want, I can now:\n👉 Take **mock interview**\n\n* I ask question\n* You write query\n* I correct + optimize + explain deeply\n\nThis is the fastest way to master.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n\n---\n\n# 🧩 SETUP (Assume Models)\n\nclass User(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n    age = models.IntegerField()\n\nclass Product(models.Model):\n    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n    price = models.FloatField()\n\nclass Order(models.Model):\n    user = models.ForeignKey(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    created_at = models.DateTimeField()\n\nclass OrderItem(models.Model):\n    order = models.ForeignKey(Order, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    product = models.ForeignKey(Product, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    quantity = models.IntegerField()\n\n---\n\n# 🟡 LEVEL 1 (Core Understanding)\n\n### 1. Get all users whose age > 25\nUser.objects.filter(age__gt=25)\n\n\n### 2. Get users whose name contains \"amit\"\nUser.objects.filter(name__icontains=\"amit\")\n\n\n### 3. Get latest 5 orders\nOrder.objects.order_by(\"-created_at\")[:5]\n\n### 4. Count total users\nUser.objects.count()\n\n### 5. Get all product names only\nProduct.objects.values_list(\"name\", flat=True)\n\n\n\n# 🟠 LEVEL 2 (JOINS & RELATIONSHIPS)\n\n### 6. Get all orders for user \"Amit\"\nOrder.objects.filter(user__name=\"Amit\")\n\n\n### 7. Get users who have placed at least 1 order\nUser.objects.filter(order__isnull=False).distinct()\n\n\n### 8. Get users with NO orders\nUser.objects.filter(order__isnull=True)\n\n\n### 9. Get all order items where product price > 100\nOrderItem.objects.filter(product__price__gt=100)\n\n\n### 10. Fetch orders with user data optimized\nOrder.objects.select_related(\"user\")\n\n\n🔵 LEVEL 3 (AGGREGATION & GROUP BY)\n\n### 11. Count orders per user\nfrom django.db.models import Count\nUser.objects.annotate(order_count=Count(\"order\"))\n\n\n### 12. Users with more than 3 orders\nUser.objects.annotate(order_count=Count(\"order\"))\\\n            .filter(order_count__gt=3)\n\n\n### 13. Total quantity sold per product\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    total_sold=Count(\"orderitem\")\n)\n\n\n👉 (Better version below 👇)\nfrom django.db.models import Sum\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    total_sold=Sum(\"orderitem__quantity\")\n)\n\n\n### 14. Average product price\nfrom django.db.models import Avg\nProduct.objects.aggregate(avg_price=Avg(\"price\"))\n\n\n### 15. Total revenue per order\nfrom django.db.models import Sum, F\n\nOrder.objects.annotate(\n    total=Sum(F(\"orderitem__quantity\") * F(\"orderitem__product__price\"))\n)\n\n\n🔴 LEVEL 4 (ADVANCED QUERIES 🔥)\n\n### 16. Get latest order per user\n\nfrom django.db.models import OuterRef, Subquery\n\nlatest_order = Order.objects.filter(user=OuterRef(\"pk\"))\\\n                            .order_by(\"-created_at\")\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    latest_order_id=Subquery(latest_order.values(\"id\")[:1])\n)\n\n\n### 17. Users who ordered a specific product\nUser.objects.filter(order__orderitem__product__name=\"Laptop\").distinct()\n\n\n### 18. Orders with total > 1000\nOrder.objects.annotate(\n    total=Sum(F(\"orderitem__quantity\") * F(\"orderitem__product__price\"))\n).filter(total__gt=1000)\n\n\n### 19. Products never ordered\nProduct.objects.filter(orderitem__isnull=True)\n\n\n### 20. Users with at least 1 expensive product (>500)\nUser.objects.filter(\n    order__orderitem__product__price__gt=500\n).distinct()\n\n\n# ⚡ LEVEL 5 (EXPERT 🔥🔥🔥)\n\n### 21. Users whose total spending > 5000\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    total_spent=Sum(\n        F(\"order__orderitem__quantity\") *\n        F(\"order__orderitem__product__price\")\n    )\n).filter(total_spent__gt=5000)\n\n\n### 22. Most sold product\n\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    total_sold=Sum(\"orderitem__quantity\")\n).order_by(\"-total_sold\").first()\n\n\n### 23. Users who placed order in last 7 days\n\nfrom django.utils import timezone\nfrom datetime import timedelta\n\nUser.objects.filter(\n    order__created_at__gte=timezone.now() - timedelta(days=7)\n).distinct()\n\n\n### 24. Orders having more than 3 items\nOrder.objects.annotate(\n    item_count=Count(\"orderitem\")\n).filter(item_count__gt=3)\n\n\n### 25. Products with highest revenue\n\nProduct.objects.annotate(\n    revenue=Sum(\n        F(\"orderitem__quantity\") * F(\"price\")\n    )\n).order_by(\"-revenue\")\n\n\n\n### 26. Check if user has orders (efficient)\nfrom django.db.models import Exists, OuterRef\n\norders = Order.objects.filter(user=OuterRef(\"pk\"))\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    has_orders=Exists(orders)\n)\n\n\n### 27. Get first order date per user\nfrom django.db.models import Min\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    first_order=Min(\"order__created_at\")\n)\n\n\n### 28. Users who bought ALL products (hard)\n\n👉 Concept: count match\n\n\nfrom django.db.models import Count\n\ntotal_products = Product.objects.count()\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    product_count=Count(\"order__orderitem__product\", distinct=True)\n).filter(product_count=total_products)\n\n\n### 29. Duplicate users by name\n\nUser.objects.values(\"name\")\\\n    .annotate(count=Count(\"id\"))\\\n    .filter(count__gt=1)\n\n\n### 30. Top 3 users by spending\n\nUser.objects.annotate(\n    total_spent=Sum(\n        F(\"order__orderitem__quantity\") *\n        F(\"order__orderitem__product__price\")\n    )\n).order_by(\"-total_spent\")[:3]\n\n\n\n# 🧠 HOW TO MASTER (IMPORTANT)\n\nIf you truly want to reach **“I can write anything” level**, follow this:\n\n### 🔁 Practice Loop\n\n1. Convert problem → SQL\n2. SQL → ORM\n3. Optimize query\n\n---\n\n### 🔥 Key Patterns You Must Master\n\n* `filter(user__order__...)` → JOIN chaining\n* `annotate()` → GROUP BY\n* `Subquery + OuterRef` → nested queries\n* `Exists` → performance optimization\n* `F()` → field vs field operations\n\n---\n\n# 🚀 NEXT STEP (Highly Recommended)\n\nIf you want, I can now:\n👉 Take **mock interview**\n\n* I ask question\n* You write query\n* I correct + optimize + explain deeply\n\nThis is the fastest way to master.\n",
